indrical axis is the Cartesian <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-s=
tyle:italic;">z</span>-axis. Then the <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D=
"font-style:italic;">z</span>-coordinate is the same in both systems, and t=
he correspondence between cylindrical <span class=3D"texhtml">(<i>=CF=81</i=
>, <i>=CF=86</i>, <i>z</i>)</span> and Cartesian <span class=3D"texhtml">(<=
i>x</i>, <i>y</i>, <i>z</i>)</span> are the same as for polar coordinates, =
